<layoutStyles><![CDATA[<style type="text/css">.oli-dnd-table{display:table;text-align:center}.dnd-row{display:table-row}.dnd-row-header{font-weight:600;background-color:#cacaca;text-align:center}.dnd-cell{display:table-cell;padding:4px}.target{min-width:50px;min-height:50px;padding:4px;border:1px dashed #999}.initiator{color:#58646c;border:2px solid transparent;padding:6px;display:inline-block;font-size:14px;box-shadow:2px 2px 10px 0 rgba(155,165,173,1);border-radius:5px;white-space:nowrap;margin:5px;background-color:#E7F4FE;cursor:grab;cursor:-webkit-grab;user-select:none}.initiator::before{content:"";display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin-right:4px;width:12px;height:24px;background-image:-webkit-repeating-radial-gradient(center center,rgba(0,0,0,.2),rgba(0,0,0,.3) 1px,transparent 1px,transparent 100%);background-repeat:repeat;background-size:4px 4px}.initiator:active{cursor:grabbing;cursor:-webkit-grabbing}</style>]]></layoutStyles><targetArea><![CDATA[<div class="oli-dnd-table"><div class="dnd-row dnd-row-header"><div class="dnd-cell">Type of neurons</div><div class="dnd-cell">Classification</div><div class="dnd-cell">Description</div></div><div class="dnd-row"><div input_ref="targeta" class="dnd-cell target"></div><div class="dnd-cell">Structural</div><div class="dnd-cell">One cytoplasmic process extends from the cell body, and then splits with the dendrites or receptive end on one end and the rest of the process considered the axon.</div></div><div class="dnd-row"><div input_ref="targetb" class="dnd-cell target"></div><div class="dnd-cell">Structural</div><div class="dnd-cell">Two often very short cytoplasmic processes extend from the cell body; one is an axon and the other a dendrite.</div></div><div class="dnd-row"><div input_ref="targetc" class="dnd-cell target"></div><div class="dnd-cell">Structural</div><div class="dnd-cell">Contains many cytoplasmic processes connected to the cell body, only one is an axon and the rest are dendrites.</div></div><div class="dnd-row"><div input_ref="targetd" class="dnd-cell target"></div><div class="dnd-cell">Structural</div><div class="dnd-cell">Contain several cytoplasmic processes. The axon cannot be distinguished from dendrites.</div></div><div class="dnd-row"><div input_ref="targete" class="dnd-cell target"></div><div class="dnd-cell">Functional</div><div class="dnd-cell">Transmit sensory information from peripheral sensory receptors towards the central nervous system.</div></div><div class="dnd-row"><div input_ref="targetf" class="dnd-cell target"></div><div class="dnd-cell">Functional</div><div class="dnd-cell">Process information within the central nervous system and link sensory neurons to motor neurons.</div></div><div class="dnd-row"><div input_ref="targetg" class="dnd-cell target"></div><div class="dnd-cell">Functional</div><div class="dnd-cell">Carry motor commands from the central nervous system to the target tissues like muscles or glands.</div></div></div>]]></targetArea><initiators><![CDATA[<div input_val="initiatora" class="initiator">Unipolar neurons</div><div input_val="initiatorb" class="initiator">Bipolar neurons</div><div input_val="initiatorc" class="initiator">Multipolar neurons</div><div input_val="initiatord" class="initiator">Anaxonic neurons</div><div input_val="initiatore" class="initiator">Sensory (afferent) neurons</div><div input_val="initiatorf" class="initiator">Interneurons</div><div input_val="initiatorg" class="initiator">Motor (efferent) neurons</div>]]></initiators></dragdrop>
